post_text:
Last night the Board of Education approved its 2020-2021 budget.

We continue to spend responsibly to prioritize our students:

🖤Acquiring New Land Adjacent to High School
💛Spartan Stadium Renovation
🖤New Spartan School of Art Academy
💛More Reading Resources for our youngest students
🖤7 New School Buses
💛Renovation of HS Library for New Sharon
🖤New Marching Band Uniforms
💛New Paving at High School
🖤Relocation of HS Weight Room
💛Technology & Maintenance Upgrades

All this is in addition to upgraded & new facilities and increased efficiencies from the Spartan Improvement Plan.

Click the link below for the approved budget presentation.

https://www.deptfordschools.org/ourpages/auto/2019/4/22/56649599/2020-21%20Budget%20Presentation.pdf

The Unforgotten Haven
April 17 at 9:24 AM ·

We will be accepting donations of Non Perishable Food tomorrow Saturday April 18th, 2020 from10am to 11am..
At 12pm to 1pm is our FREE food giveaway to those in need...
It will be raining but the distribution will still take place.❤
There are so many people in need at this time..
Just be sure the food is not expired.❤
Thank You to ALL who have been supporting us through this pandemic...
If you would like to make a monetary donation toward food me and Ethel will be shipping early tomorrow morning.
Just go to PayPal
Enter our Email Address
Theunforgottenhaven@comcast.net
*please write food pantry in note so we know where to apply your funds!!❤

post_text:
We're happy to partner with Deptford Township Police Department and NJ State PBA to host a drive-through COVID-19 testing site at Deptford High School for First Responders 🖤💛

This testing site is by appointment only and open only to first responders: front-line healthcare workers, members of law enforcement, fire personnel, paramedics, & EMTs.

Hours of operation are 8:00 AM - 1:00 PM on select days.

First responders can make an appointment online by visiting: https://njpba.adlabscovidtest.com/

One Simple Wish
March 17 at 8:00 AM ·

Contact us if you are in foster care, or aged out,
and you need a laptop for remote learning. Please note that this is for young people in foster care or those that aged out that need a laptop for schoolwork. We are doing our best to get these wishes granted first and then can take others that are not for immediate school needs.
Please share as your status 💙
AND IF YOU CAN DONATE TO SUPPORT THIS EFFORT, please go to onesimplewish.org/education
Requests are pouring in!

Archway Programs
January 6 at 6:00 PM ·

Robin Holmes, Upper School Paraprofessional, rides the bus before and after school. The bus staff she rides with, Deptford Bus #60, both made donations to our Upper School during the holiday season. After hearing Robin talk about the holiday dinner baskets that staff puts together for students and their families, they decided to get involved themselves. Thank you to Pam Cox and Sonia McCloskey for your generosity this holiday season. Collectively they donated turkeys, cases of canned goods and fourteen Walmart gift cards for our older students. Pictured here is Archway’s Upper School Principal Mark Letiziano, Sonia McCloskey, Robin Holmes and Pam Cox. Thank you Robin for always thinking about our students! #ArchwayProud #ArchwayFamily #ArchwaySchools #specialeducation #NJDOE #HelpingThoseInNeed
